<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PUSH TO RECYCLE OUR MOUNTAINS OF TRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We have always recycled our newspapers to save the trees. Now, for the first 
time, I can't recycle. At $5 a ton, it is not worth it to the recycler and his 
receiver. They are refusing to accept newspapers. 
</P>
<P>
I have canceled my daily paper and kept it Sunday, only because I can't stand 
to give up The Times completely. 
</P>
<P>
The idea of recycling has struggled so hard to survive and catch on. We can't 
lose that momentum, if only because the dumps are filling up so fast. 
</P>
<P>
GRACE GAFFNEY 
</P>
<P>
Yucca Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
