<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROSE SIMPLY BETTING HE'LL BE REINSTATED; PUBLIC DESERVES MORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A hearty thank you to Ross Newhan for having the guts to say he will not vote 
for Pete Rose's induction into the Baseball Hall of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
I had hoped there would be more than one sportswriter who would speak out 
before waiting to see how strong public opinion was swinging. 
</P>
<P>
Newhan is right, Rose could have made it easier on himself by showing a little 
bit of humility. The fans were ready to give him the benefit of a doubt until 
that final inning in front of the TV cameras. 
</P>
<P>
That's when Pete made his last strikeout. 
</P>
<P>
ALLAN BENJAMIN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
