<P>
ROSE 'SHOCKED' BY THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert Pitcairn Jr., one of Pete Rose's attorneys, spoke with the former 
cincinnati Reds manager by telephone about Commissioner A. Bartlett Giamatti's 
death Friday. 
</P>
<P>
"Pete is deeply saddened by the news," Pitcairn said. "He extends his deepest 
sympathy to Commissioner Giamatti's family." 
</P>
<P>
Asked Rose's initial reaction to the news, Pitcairn said: "He was shocked, just 
as we all were." 
</P>
