<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABC UNIT DEVELOPING PAIR OF SHOWS FOR NBC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KAYE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABC's new television production arm is developing two shows for NBC, apparently 
marking the first time one network has agreed to create programming for 
another. 
</P>
<P>
One of the proposed programs is a miniseries and the other a series, said 
Brandon Stoddard, the former ABC Entertainment president who now heads the 
fledgling ABC Productions unit. He said no firm deals have been made to produce 
the shows. 
</P>
<P>
The in-house production division has 18 projects in development, Stoddard said 
at a Century City news conference Friday, with a miniseries and two movies in 
the works for HBO, two movies in development for the Lifetime cable network, 
which is partially owned by Capital Cities/ABC, and the rest slated for ABC. 
JEFF KAYE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ABC PRODUCTIONS; NBC TELEVISION NETWORK; TELEVISION NETWORKS; TELEVISION 
PRODUCERS; TELEVISION PROGRAMMING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
