<HEADLINE>
<P>
LABOR DAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday is Labor Day, the unofficial "end of summer." The following will be 
closed in observance of the holiday: 
</P>
<P>
All city, county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
Schools, including colleges and universities. 
</P>
<P>
County, state and federal courthouses 
</P>
<P>
City and county libraries 
</P>
<P>
Banks and savings and loan institutions 
</P>
<P>
MAIL: Post offices also will be closed. Mail deposited in mailboxes will be 
picked up according to the posted holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
TRASH: There will be no trash pickup by city or county refuse workers Monday. 
Trash pickup will be a day late the rest of the week. 
</P>
<P>
OCTD: Orange County Transit District buses will run on a holiday schedule 
Monday. There will be no dial-a-ride and car-pool services available. 
</P>
<P>
PARKS: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
regular hours Monday. 
</P>
