<P>
SOBRIETY CHECKPOINT PROGRAM STARTS SEPT. 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police will begin a program of setting up sobriety checkpoints with officers 
from other communities beginning in Los Alamitos Sept. 15. 
</P>
<P>
The task force is composed of officers from Seal Beach, La Palma and Cypress as 
well as from Los Alamitos, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The check points will be rotated among the four communities. 
</P>
<P>
During the stops, officers will hand out pamphlets on drunk driving. 
</P>
<P>
Money for the program is from a grant by the California Office of Traffic 
Safety. 
</P>
